<title>CANADA: CGI Group splits shares two-for-one.</title>
<headline>CGI Group splits shares two-for-one.</headline>
<dateline>MONTREAL 1997-06-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>CGI Group Inc said on Thursday its board of directors had resolved to split the information technology firm's Class A shares on a two-for-one basis to provide greater liquidity.</p>
<p>The move must be approved by shareholders at a meeting in July.</p>
<p>CGI shares closed at C$25.75 on the Toronto Stock Exchange on Thursday, up from a year low of C$5.50.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100))</p>
